Data Preparation:

Data Augmentation:

Create more data by applying transformations like rotations, flips, zooms, and shifts to existing images. This increases dataset size and diversity, improving the model's generalization.

Normalization:

Rescaling pixel values (e.g., from 0-255 to 0-1) helps the CNN converge faster and perform better by standardizing the input range.

Class Imbalance Handling:

If the dataset is unbalanced (e.g., more fighter-jet images than missile), techniques like oversampling the minority class or undersampling the majority class help avoid model bias.

Cross-Validation:

Perform cross-validation, where the dataset is split into multiple folds, ensuring that the model is evaluated across various subsets of the data, improving robustness.

Shuffling Data:

Shuffle the dataset before splitting to ensure random distribution of data across train, validation, and test sets. This prevents patterns in the data order from influencing model performance.

size = min(len(fighter_fnames), len(missile_fnames), len(helicopter_fnames))


train_size = int(np.floor(0.7 * size))
valid_size = int(np.floor(0.2 * size))
test_size = size - train_size - valid_size

train_idx = train_size
valid_idx = train_size + valid_size
test_idx = train_size + valid_size + test_size

Data Augmentation (train_datagen):

Various transformations are applied to the training images to artificially increase the diversity of the training dataset. These include:

  • rotation_range: Rotating images randomly by up to 45 degrees.
  • rescale: Scaling pixel values to the range [0, 1] by dividing by 255.
  • width_shift_range & height_shift_range: Randomly shifting images horizontally and vertically by up to 25%.
  • shear_range: Randomly applying a shear transformation (like slanting) by 30%.
  • zoom_range: Randomly zooming in/out on the images by up to 30%.
  • horizontal_flip: Randomly flipping the image horizontally.
  • fill_mode: Filling in any missing pixels created by transformations using the nearest pixel values.

Rescaling for Validation (valid_datagen):

No augmentations are applied to validation data. The images are simply rescaled by dividing pixel values by 255, ensuring they are normalized.

Creating Generators (train_generator and valid_generator):

These generators load images from directories (train_dir and valid_dir), resize them to 150x150 pixels, and generate batches of 32 images at a time. The class_mode='categorical' option indicates that the model will be used for multi-class classification. This setup enables the model to learn from augmented training data while using the validation data only for evaluation without transformations.

In[]:
train_datagen = ImageDataGenerator(
    rotation_range=45,  
    rescale=1./255.,
    width_shift_range=0.25,
    height_shift_range=0.25, 
    shear_range=0.3,     
    zoom_range=0.3,   
    horizontal_flip=True, 
    fill_mode='nearest' 
)


valid_datagen = ImageDataGenerator(rescale=1./255.)

train_generator = train_datagen.flow_from_directory(directory=train_dir,
                                                   target_size=(150, 150),
                                                   batch_size=32,
                                                   class_mode='categorical')

valid_generator = valid_datagen.flow_from_directory(directory=valid_dir,
                                                   target_size=(150, 150),
                                                   batch_size=32,
                                                   class_mode='categorical')

def display_augmented_images(directory, idx):
    fnames = [os.path.join(directory, fname) for fname in os.listdir(directory)]
    img_path = fnames[idx]
    img = image.load_img(img_path, target_size=(150, 150))

    x = image.img_to_array(img)
    x = x.reshape((1, ) + x.shape)

    i = 1
    plt.figure(figsize=(16, 8))
    for batch in train_datagen.flow(x, batch_size=1):
        plt.subplot(3, 4, i)
        plt.grid(False)
        imgplot = plt.imshow(image.array_to_img(batch[0]))
        i += 1
        if i % 13 == 0:
            break
